<h2> Definition </h2>

The <strong>@HI{{ko}}-</strong> demonstratives generally relate to something near to the speaker, either physically or emotionally.
<p></p>

The <strong>@HI{{so}}-</strong> demonstratives generally relate to something near to the listener. They can be used to
refer to something that is not close to either the speaker or the listener if information about that
thing has already been provided.
<p></p>

The <strong>@HI{{a}}-</strong> demonstratives generally relate to something that is not near to either the speaker
or the listener.
<p></p>

The <strong>@HI{{do}}-</strong> demonstratives refer to something about which a question is being asked.
<p></p>

<strong>@HI{{kore}}</strong>, <strong>@HI{{sore}}</strong> and <strong>@HI{{are}}</strong> are demonstratives and function as pronouns.
<p></p>

<strong>@HI{{kono}}</strong>, <strong>@HI{{sono}}</strong> and <strong>@HI{{ano}}</strong> are pre-noun adjectivals and serve to modify a noun. <strong>@HI{{dono}}</strong> is used with a following noun to ask "which" noun.
<p></p>

<strong>@HI{{donnna}}</strong> is used with a following noun to mean "what kind of".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{<strong>sore</strong>ha}}@KJ{{resign}}@KJ{{write}}@HI{{desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Is that a dictionary?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{<strong>kore</strong>wo kudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Please give me this one.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{<strong>kono</strong>}}@KJ{{book}}@HI{{ha}}@KJ{{private}}@HI{{nodesu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This book is mine.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{<strong>ano</strong>}}@KJ{{direction}}@HI{{ha donata desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Who is that (person)?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @KJ{{nara}}@KJ{{good}}@HI{{ha <strong>donnna</strong>}}@KJ{{town}}@HI{{desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What kind of town is Nara?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @KT{{santosu}}@HI{{sanha <strong>dono</strong>}}@KJ{{person}}@HI{{desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Which one is Mr. Santos?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

